      • makeBetterDisplayName

        public static String makeBetterDisplayName(String colName)
        Tries to represent column name as some text label for column:

        1. Column name may contain "___": then "___" will be removed.

        2. Each group of lowercase symbols, started with uppercase symbols, comprehends as word, and this group separated from other group with spaces. Example: "groupCombineInformation" will be converted to "group Combine Information"

        3. Tries to find words, delimited by '_' symbol. All of '_' symbols exchanged for spaces, and each resulting word will be rewritten with first uppercase letter.

        If second and third case was ineffective, then this method looks if some of words, specified below, ends the string, and then founded word will be separated with the space:

        "id", "phone", "number", "background", "name", "value", "column", "description", "code", "type", "size", "begin", "end", "price"
        Parameters:
        colName - column Name
        Returns:
        formatted text label
